author: Kale Williams
title: S.F. mansion squatter pleads not guilty to burglary, theft
text:
Photo: SFC / Kale Williams Jeremiah Kaylor, photographed during an interview in San Francisco jail on Oct. 20, 2015, was arrested on suspicion of squatting in a historic Presidio Heights mansion and selling off its artwork. Jeremiah Kaylor, photographed during an interview in San Francisco...
A homeless man who set up camp in a historic but vacant mansion in San Francisco’s Presidio Heights — perhaps because of an obsession with pop star Taylor Swift — pleaded not guilty Wednesday to five felonies for selling off pricey paintings he found inside.
